<p>Learned <a href="https://social.jacobian.org/@jacob/113357737335237134">via</a> Jacob Kaplan-Moss today that now Python has a way to specify dependencies inline in scripts?! For example I can create this script:</p>
<pre><code># /// script
# requires-python = &quot;&gt;=3.9&quot;
# dependencies = [
#   &quot;requests&lt;3&quot;,
# ]
# ///
import requests
requests.get(&quot;http://example.com&quot;)
</code></pre>
<p>and then run it with <code>uv run blah.py</code>. I haven&rsquo;t totally understood what&rsquo;s going on with <code>uv</code> yet but it seems interesting. The syntax is <a href="https://packaging.python.org/en/latest/specifications/inline-script-metadata/#inline-script-metadata">documented here</a>, some <a href="https://simonwillison.net/tags/uv/">notes on uv from @simonw here</a></p>
